CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. B7, reads: "PROFESSIONALS - Sterling James Robinson Jr., and Joseph Saunders Ellison, became dentists upon receiving their Doctors of Dental Surgery Degrees...Dr. Ellison also received the undergraduate degree of Bachelor of Science, which he earned last August."
TitMainTitle: Sterling James Robinson Jr. and Joseph Saunders Ellison wearing suits and holding rolled documents after receiving Doctor of Dental Surgery Degrees, posed in front of Cathedral of Learning, at University of Pittsburgh graduation, Oakland
